Sincere question: “why” is this bullish?

Is there a unique adoption path that edge is enabling? Onboarding still strikes me as primary hurdle. Most onboarding paths involve fiat -> crypto via a CEX and then someone being “sophisticated” enough to take on the risk of transferring to a non-custodial experience.

I don’t disagree, but on an impact basis, I believe we need more primary utilization paths + reduced friction in onboarding / adoption instead of web2/big tech “co-signing”.

Counter: if this wallet will enable unique integrated experiences for MSFT gaming community, THAT could be cool + organic ecosystem growth.
